"'''Tilotny Throws a Shape'''" is a comic story written by [[Alan Moore]] and originally published in Marvel UK's [[The Empire Strikes Back Monthly 154|''The Empire Strikes Back Monthly'' 154]]. It was later reprinted and colorized in [[Classic Star Wars: Devilworlds 2|''Classic Star Wars: Devilworlds'' 2]].

==Plot summary==
After being forced to land on an [[Bedlam/Legends|unidentified planet]], Princess [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] tries to [[Mission to Bedlam|escape]] from pursuing [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] troops. She stumbles upon the remains of some Imperial [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]] that had been lying there for thousands of [[Standard year/Legends|years]]. Meanwhile, a [[Bedlam Spirits|spirit]] called [[Tilotny]] "throws a shape" and is followed by three more spirits. Leia soon meets them, along with three stormtroopers. Tilotny decides to play with them, and kills one stormtrooper by turning him into a [[Diamond/Legends|diamond]]. After that she turns Leia's [[Heart/Legends|heart]] into a diamond too and mixes the remaining stormtroopers together. After being tired from playing, Tilotny leaves the spirit called [[Splendid Ap]] to restore everything to normal. Splendid Ap revives the four beings, but not being aware of the concept of [[Time/Legends|time]], mistakenly [[Time travel/Legends|places]] the stormtroopers [[8000 BBY|eight thousand years in the past]]. It was the remains of these stormtroopers that Leia discovered.

==Continuity==
{{Quote|My leg's almost ''healed'' since it was injured on that last mission...|Leia Organa to Han Solo|<ref name="sw35">[[Star Wars (1977) 35|''Star Wars'' (1977) 35]]</ref>
}}
Leia Organa injures her ankle in this comic. She appears with a bandaged ankle in [[Star Wars (1977) 35|''Star Wars'' (1977) 35]].

